Novelty. The specific combination of (i) betting-based confidence sequences, (ii) LTT monotone sweep for multiple testing, and (iii) cross-domain transfer via warm-started wealth processes constitutes a three-way novelty not present in the literature. Prior work on transfer learning for conformal prediction (Vovk et al., 2005) uses different mechanisms (transductive conformal), and prior work on betting (Waudby-Smith and Ramdas, 2024) does not consider cross-domain settings. The dominance guarantee (Theorem 1), convergence rate (Corollary 1), and optimality result (Proposition 2) together establish that TIB is not merely “plugging a prior into GROW” but a principled transfer mechanism with provable benefits.
