The marginal risk formulation (Eq. 1) averages over all intents. A deployment concern is that some intents may have elevated error rates masked by the aggregate guarantee. We test per-intent RCPS by running the bound within each intent class independently (, ).
On MASSIVE (Figure 5(a)), only check_calendar (, accuracy 92.2%) achieves a subgroup guarantee: LTT + Bernstein yields with 60.7% coverage and test risk of only 0.6%. Hoeffding + union bound is infeasible even for this largest class. The remaining 7 intents have —below the threshold identified in Section 6.4.
